article.headline: Marist 84, Old Dominion 71
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. (AP) -- Jared Jordan had 26 points and Will Whittington scored 24 to lead Marist in an 84-71 win over Old Dominion Wednesday night. Marist improved to 5-2 overall with the win, while the Monarchs fell to 5-2. Marist took its largest first half lead of 29-19 on a 3-pointer by Smith. The Monarchs' bench outscored Marist 12-0 in the first stanza, but was behind the Red Foxes 40-33 at the half. The Red Foxes put the game out of reach with a 23-6 run over the first nine minutes of the half to go up 63-39 on a tip-in by Shae McNamara. The Monarchs got no closer than a 13-point deficit the rest of the way. James Smith scored 19 points and had 11 rebounds for Marist (5-2). Valdas Vasylius had 15 points and Brian Henderson scored 14 for Old Dominion. Marist shot 48.4 percent from the field, while Old Dominion made 46.2 percent of its shots. The Red Foxes outrebounded Old Dominion 37-28.
